let S2;
func S1 + S2 -> (Element of ( V .. W ))
means
:Def15: ((S1 = ( a1 .. W ) & S2 = ( a2 .. W )) implies it = ( ( a1 + a2 ) .. W ));
existence
proof
consider a1 such that A6: S1 = ( a1 .. W ) by CKB42:1;
consider a2 such that A7: S2 = ( a2 .. W ) by CKB42:1;
A8:now
let b1 being (Vector of V),b2 being (Vector of V);
assume that
A9: S1 = ( b1 .. W )
and
A10: S2 = ( b2 .. W );
A11: ( a1 - b1 ) in W by A6,A9,CKB38:1;
( a2 - b2 ) in W by A7,A10,CKB38:1;
then A12: ( ( a1 - b1 ) + ( a2 - b2 ) ) in W by A11,VECTSP_4:20;
( ( a1 - b1 ) + ( a2 - b2 ) ) = ( ( ( a1 - b1 ) + a2 ) - b2 ) by RLVECT_1:def 3
.= ( ( ( a1 + a2 ) - b1 ) - b2 ) by CKB11:1
.= ( ( a1 + a2 ) - ( b1 + b2 ) ) by VECTSP_1:17;
hence ( ( a1 + a2 ) .. W ) = ( ( b1 + b2 ) .. W ) by A12,CKB38:1;
end;
take ( ( a1 + a2 ) .. W );
thus thesis by A8;
end;
uniqueness
proof
let S being (Element of ( V .. W )),T being (Element of ( V .. W ));
assume that
A13: ((S1 = ( a1 .. W ) & S2 = ( a2 .. W )) implies S = ( ( a1 + a2 ) .. W ))
and
A14: ((S1 = ( a1 .. W ) & S2 = ( a2 .. W )) implies T = ( ( a1 + a2 ) .. W ));
consider a1 such that A15: S1 = ( a1 .. W ) by CKB42:1;
consider a2 such that A16: S2 = ( a2 .. W ) by CKB42:1;
thus S = ( ( a1 + a2 ) .. W ) by A13,A15,A16
.= T by A14,A15,A16;
end;
